ty that exists among Canadians and their calls for structural and operational reforms. By illuminating the symbiotic relationship between the Crown, Senate, and Commons, The Constitution in a Hall of Mirrors brings government reform closer to reality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Canadian.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066594940uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148751540940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487515409423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487515409.jpg  a978-3-11-066594-9  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles